    • playSound

      private void playSound(int sound)
      This method takes in an int representing the sound effect to be played and will use GameController's backgroundMusic method to play the sound.

      This method is ran any time the puck collides with a wall or any paddle. Sound effect 1 plays the point sound when a point is obtained by either player. Sound effect 2 will play the sound anytime the puck hits any colidable object.

      Parameters:
      sound - an int representing the sfx to be played
